<! [CDATA[
Adobe Fonts Logo
Adobe Fonts is an online service that provides its subscribers with access to its font library, under a single licensing agreement.. The fonts may be used directly on websites, or synced via Adobe Creative Cloud to applications on the subscriber’s computers. Adobe Fonts was launched as Typekit in November 2009 by Small Batch, Inc., a company run by creators of the Google Analytics service. In October 2011, the service was acquired by Adobe.
You can download theAdobe Fontslogo on full-version of the page.
